

     
      "Once somebody is a Sensei, it is proper protocol to refer to them as Sensei, whether it is on the mats or off the mats, they are always Sensei. However, protocol also says that if you do not respect that person as Sensei, never call him Sensei, not once not ever. "   -- Steven Seagal, 7th dan, Shihan, Shinto priest 
     
    
